HEADWORD: clitter
<hw>clitter</hw> <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>to make a shrill creaking noise
by rubbing together special bodily structures, as of male insects such
as crickets or grasshoppers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> stridulate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

